<subSubSection id="7198EB09FE0885285E20CD8C82E948E1" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="6303E49988C5D0A8CBC33AD5B2844CDB" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9637D924417FEB3C546754D9F0ECD77A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">With head in full-face view, lateral margins of head anterior to eye level parallel and lacking erect hairs, lateral and anteromedian clypeal margins continuously forming broad convexity; scape without erect hairs; mesosoma long and low; body color yellowish to brown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9F5DF5527C7049B262A8733FAD9B466F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="61F54FD21EF38F306FD10ABD6218A84A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0B87D70DF0C7C6CD45C7A18409CD9202" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="74FB527309CE6D8A14DCC266E02325E8" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Minor worker.</emphasis>
In full-face view, head sides anterior to level of eye parallel, rounding evenly to posterior margin behind eye level; eye protruding and large (EL/CS: 0.32
<normalizedToken id="4DDD34FC608BD92E10A16B8B94936283" originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
0.01; 0.30-0.35), breaking lateral cephalic margin, level of its posterior margin situated approximately at posterior 1/4 of head (PoOc/CL: 0.23
<normalizedToken id="987FA8483B5570E0C7772DB7C6DF36A6" originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
0.01; 0.20-0.24); frontal carinae close to each other (FR/CS: 0.27
<normalizedToken id="F508DB229A8DC01332EBFE2208B82C5E" originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
0.01; 0.25-0.28), posteriorly parallel, distance between them smaller than their smallest distance to eye; clypeus without well-defined anterolateral angle, its anteromedian margin broadly convex; mandible with two apical teeth normally spaced; antennal scape relatively long (SL/CS: 1.40
<normalizedToken id="C22853E3B466FB793968DB7373A2E64D" originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
0.04; 1.33-1.45). Promesonotum weakly convex; mesonotum with posterior portion flat immediately anterior to weakly visible metanotal groove; propodeal dorsum almost straight (MPH/ML: 0.37
<normalizedToken id="82D2B18EED8BD2595EBCC9469B125AAA" originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
0.03; 0.34-0.50); rounding to declivity, 2 
<normalizedToken id="8657B04E325FD4BAF76EE96AB60D82D0" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as declivity. Petiolar node short and high, with dorsal margin inclined posteriorly, rounding to anterior margin; height of anterior face 2/3 of that of posterior face; femur of hind leg rounded axially, without twist near base.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="25722FC250B467670E2F7C53D80E10FE" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">First and second gastral tergites without a pair of white spots; lateral margin of head anterior to eye level, with no erect hairs posterior to eye level; two erect hairs present close to posterior margin; antennal scape covered only with appressed hairs; erect hairs lacking on promesonotum; posterodorsal corner of propodeum with a pair of erect hairs. Integument shining; body color yellowish.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D6FEB113465CD094EC6B5C06BB753DB7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="6A9A34894913FA09760EF5EB8429FD9D" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Major worker.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="AE26BADC11D3C6F48D7706894B3C7569" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="345F86336D2D0EDBD475E81B1EFF297F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution and biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C40DA701188C9E5942199C0C2AFFA2E6" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="85CD5D382F72B35764EC521F3AA1A794" authorityName="Rakotonirina &amp; Fisher" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Camponotus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Camponotus mahafaly" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mahafaly">
<emphasis id="90E490D13BF3EEC84AECEF7DE0AC4723" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Camponotus mahafaly</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is geographically restricted to dry forest and spiny bush and forest habitats of the southwest and south of Madagascar (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6828D4321B9BA2CD10C4F47079C6D2F5" captionStart="Figure 66" captionStartId="F66" captionText="Figure 66. Camponotus mahafaly A lateral view B head in full-face view C dorsal view of minor worker CASENT 0115287 D distribution map." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1098.73223.figure66" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/678125" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">66D</figureCitation>
). Nest sites are generally located in rotten logs, and foraging occurs on the surface of the ground.
</paragraph>
<caption id="BB57D7E4A14069DAEF59F7FDCC600C15" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1098.73223.figure66" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/678125" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Figure 66" startId="F66">
<paragraph id="F8D6109BC3514DEC349E333E781BB8FD" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="B59F8916CAB3E1B00A238D8E81FADB00" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Figure 66.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="E2F4FFC8105F5311D43321CD94F81D12" authorityName="Rakotonirina &amp; Fisher" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Camponotus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Camponotus mahafaly" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mahafaly">
<emphasis id="3C018EB13A6CA0B48C5D2E09982A3C00" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Camponotus mahafaly</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="279BCC413045FC764A442DF582B8565E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A</emphasis>
lateral view 
<emphasis id="A9A011A020626B077A32BD114D37B300" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">B</emphasis>
head in full-face view 
<emphasis id="1248BF2F739D3D197FAA350FA312E579" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C</emphasis>
dorsal view of minor worker CASENT0115287 
<emphasis id="4D335D7BF289B4639EF7AF2792F9E2B4" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D</emphasis>
